{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9d3fb630-18ba-455b-a708-65f15d31cbf5","content":"Two things change with xUnit.net v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax changes\n\nMTP uses `--filter` but with **different operators**:\n\n| VSTest (v2) | MTP (v3) | Meaning |\n|---|---|---|\n| `~` (contains) | `~=` | contains |\n| `&` (and) | `&` | same |\n| `Category` | `Category` | same (traits still work) |\n\nYour new CI command:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~=IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nThe key change is **`~` → `~=`** for the \"contains\" operator.\n\n### 2. Trait attribute changes\n\nIn xUnit.net v3, `[Trait]` still works but the namespace changes from `Xunit` to `Xunit` (same name, different assembly). Your `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` will continue to work — no code change needed there.\n\n### Quick reference of MTP filter operators\n\n| Operator | Meaning |\n|---|---|\n| `=` | equals |\n| `!=` | not equals |\n| `~=` | contains |\n| `!~=` | does not contain |\n| `&` | and |\n| `\\|` | or |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ca0be79f-5f36-4bc6-a3f4-e76dca0c4a18","outputTokens":321,"requestId":"5C25:19AB05:C17DD:F0233:69F54B8C"},"id":"45db6c4b-b383-4775-aa26-3b3d8b6e31a8","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:55:48.118Z","parentId":"48074229-4a9c-44a6-92c5-93b45133d860"}
